Subject: Re: [T2] To much Oil Pressure??

At 04:14 PM 7/14/2003, Dave wrote:
>             My T4 converted to upright, with 20/50 straight oil is running
>at 60 lbs oil pressure.  Is this to much?

No.

>When
>I give it gas something is spraying oil on the header on the right side.  I
>can see it cooking off the header.  Just seem to be very slight at idle but
>when I rev it up it hits the exhaust and smokes off.  I can't seem to tell
>where it's coming from.

Check the thermostat pulley bolt hole.  It goes right into the case and if you leave the bolt out for whatever reason it will spray a very fine oil mist onto the right heat exchanger and muffler.

-David
